{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3560049,"name":"Roger","username":"Rogerr079","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/rogerr079/{size}/222096_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T01:55:28.121Z","cooked":"<p>As mentioned in the title, im trying to use a HolonomicDriveController to align to the reef. It works most of the times but sometimes it aligns to the pose correctly but does a full spin to get to the correct rotation instead of taking the shortest spin (enableContinuousInput is enabled)<br>
Here is the relevant code:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">private PIDController transController = new PIDController(5.5, 0, 0.001);
private ProfiledPIDController rotController = new ProfiledPIDController(2.5, 0, 0.1,
new TrapezoidProfile.Constraints(1, 1));
private HolonomicDriveController alignFinalController = new HolonomicDriveController(transController,transController, rotController);
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public CommandSwerveDrivetrain(

        SwerveDrivetrainConstants drivetrainConstants,
        SwerveModuleConstants&lt;?, ?, ?&gt;... modules

    ) {
        super(drivetrainConstants, modules);
        if (Utils.isSimulation()) {
            startSimThread();
        }
        configureAutoBuilder();

        alignFinalController.setTolerance(new Pose2d(.25, .25, new Rotation2d().fromDegrees(1)));
        alignFinalController.getThetaController().enableContinuousInput(Math.PI, -Math.PI);
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public ChassisSpeeds getLeftAlignSpeeds(){
    if(DriverStation.getAlliance().orElse(Alliance.Blue) == Alliance.Red){
        Pose2d closestPose = getState().Pose.nearest(Constants.RedBranches.RED_REEF_LEFT_POSES);


        return alignFinalController.calculate(getState().Pose, closestPose,0,closestPose.getRotation());
    }else{
        Pose2d closestPose = getState().Pose.nearest(Constants.BlueBranches.BLUE_REEF_LEFT_POSES);


    return alignFinalController.calculate(getState().Pose, closestPose,0,closestPose.getRotation());}
}
